\name{normalize_bx_rating_matrix}
\alias{normalize_bx_rating_matrix}
\title{Normalize BX Book Ratings Matrix}
\description{
Filters and normalizes the Book-Crossing ratings data by removing users with fewer than 10 ratings and items with fewer than 20 ratings, then converts to a normalized \code{realRatingMatrix} object.
}
\usage{
normalize_bx_rating_matrix(ratings)
}
\arguments{
  \item{ratings}{A \code{data.table} with columns: \code{user}, \code{item}, and \code{rating}. The ratings should be positive integers.}
}
\value{
A normalized \code{realRatingMatrix} object from the \code{recommenderlab} package.
}
\details{
This function filters out users who have rated fewer than 10 items and items rated by fewer than 20 users to improve data quality. Then it converts the filtered data into a \code{realRatingMatrix} and applies normalization.
}
\examples{
library(data.table)
ratings <- fread("BX-Book-Ratings.csv", sep = ";", quote = "\"", encoding = "Latin-1")
setnames(ratings, c("User-ID", "ISBN", "Book-Rating"), c("user", "item", "rating"))
ratings <- ratings[rating > 0]
norm_mat <- normalize_bx_rating_matrix(ratings)
}
